skills.name: Analytical thinking

Defining and tackling complex issues by systematically deconstructing information, be it qualitative or quantitative in nature, into manageable parts to study them and their relations.
	Formulating hypotheses and identifying additional data needed.
	Conducting analyses, drawing structured and logic conclusions, and deriving workable solutions to resolve the issues.

skills.name: Building networks and partnerships for EHS related matters
skills.description: Identifying internal (e.g., P&O, PLM; SCM; CRM) and external (e.g., industry, trade & professional associations, health insurers, regulatory bodies & agencies, universities) partners and networks relevant for achieving EHS and business objectives & aspirations Understanding their role, interests, and perspectives in relation to own EHS objectives and aspirations and determining opportunities for consultation and collaborationEstablishing trustful relationships within networks and partnerships across organizational boundaries for the purpose of enabling mutual competence enhancement and propelling “integration of EHS into business”Contributing to the ecosystem by identifying good practices across the business and broader industry and enabling learnings and opportunities for improvement Engaging with EHS community, partners and networks to enhance contemporary thinking, approaches and practices and enable this into practical application for guiding change, learning and adaptation.Representing and strengthening Siemens’ positions, interests and reputation in these networks and partnerships

skills.name: Account Management
skills.description: Making careful use of all information with regard to customer needs.Developing a strategy for value propositions to the customer.

skills.name: Account Reconciliation
skills.description: Reconciling and analyzing balance sheet accounts to ensure transactions are recorded accurately and account balances are accurately stated in accordance with IFRS, GAAP and Company policy.Researching or resolving any issues identified in the transactions.Ensuring compliance with Company Financial Standards and Procedures, and supporting efficient audit reviews from Internal and External audit.Providing process improvement ideas.Following-up andco-ordinating with HUB AC team for closure of pending actions from Balance Sheet Reconciliations review.Being responsible for on-time handling of all internal and external inquiries accurately.

skills.name: Accounting principles
skills.description: Ensuring that comprehensive and complex accounting and consolidation issues are implemented independently, cooperating with internal & external auditors, guiding & supporting businesses and directly interfaces to the customers.Basic understanding about IFRS and local GAAP and the main reasons for introducing IFRS at Siemens, relevance of IFRS for Siemens and its entities.Understanding and explaining the structure of the international and local accounting framework and applies relevant financial reporting standards to key elements of financial reports with FRG accounting know-how.Comprehensive understanding of ICFR/RIC processes and understanding of Closing & Reporting processes (Businesses/World).Expertise in standards for accounting and reporting such as the International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) and Siemens Financial Reporting Guidelines (FRG) and their application at Siemens.

skills.name: Accounting and reporting
skills.description: Measuring, processing, analyzing, and reporting of financial transactions and balances for internal and external stakeholders according to professional accounting standards and/or regulatory requirements. Providing financial and non-financial information and insights to support managerial decision-making.

skills.name: Accounting, Reporting
skills.description: Knowledge of real estate specific issues around accounting, controlling and finance.

skills.description:
Knowing and applying the processes of accounts payable - GR, IR and payments.

Knowing the match concept and the process of payment.
